"Peña E.J., Sandoval H., Zuñiga O., Torres M.","Estimates of carbon reservoirs in high-altitude wetlands in the colombian andes",2009,"Journal of Agriculture and Rural Development in the Tropics and Subtropics","110","2",,"115","126",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-73349126075&partnerID=40&md5=ec402eae301391a1a9568efc46c94280","Universidad Del Valle, Departamento de Biologfa, Facultad de Ciencias Naturales y Exactas, Calle 13 # 100-00 A.A., 25360 cali, Colombia","Peña, E.J., Universidad Del Valle, Departamento de Biologfa, Facultad de Ciencias Naturales y Exactas, Calle 13 # 100-00 A.A., 25360 cali, Colombia; Sandoval, H., Universidad Del Valle, Departamento de Biologfa, Facultad de Ciencias Naturales y Exactas, Calle 13 # 100-00 A.A., 25360 cali, Colombia; Zuñiga, O., Universidad Del Valle, Departamento de Biologfa, Facultad de Ciencias Naturales y Exactas, Calle 13 # 100-00 A.A., 25360 cali, Colombia; Torres, M., Universidad Del Valle, Departamento de Biologfa, Facultad de Ciencias Naturales y Exactas, Calle 13 # 100-00 A.A., 25360 cali, Colombia","The observed increase in emission of greenhouse gases, with attendant effects on global warming, have raised interests in identifying sources and sinks of carbon in the environment. Terrestrial carbon (C) sequestration involves capture of atmospheric C through photosynthesis and storage in biota, soil and wetlands. Particularly, wetland systems function primarily as long-term reservoirs for atmospheric carbon dioxide (CO2) and as sources of atmospheric methane (CH4). The objective of this study was to evaluate the patterns of carbon reservoirs in two high-altitude wetlands in the central Andean mountain of Colombia. Carbon cycle in both systems is related mainly with the plant biomass dynamics from the littoral zone. Thus, total organic carbon concentrate an average up to 329 kg of N ha-1 and 125 kg of P ha-1 every year vs only 17 kg N ha-1 and 6 kg P ha-1 in the water column of the limnetic zone in the wetland, evidencing spatial differences in carbon concentrations for these types of ecosystems. Results revealed that these systems participate in the balance and sequestration of carbon in the Colombian Andes.","Atmospheric carbon dioxide; Atmospheric methane; Storage in biota; Terrestrial carbon",,,,,,,"Blodau, C., Carbon cycling in peatlands - A review of processes and controls (2002) Enviorn. Rev., 10 (2), pp. 111-134; Blodau, C., Basiliko, N., Moore, R.T., Carbon turnover in peatland meso-cosms exposed to different water table levels (2004) Biogeochem., 67 (3), pp. 331-351; Bragazza, L., Siffi, C., Iacumin, P., Gerdol, R., Mass loss and nutrient release during litter decay in peatland: The role of microbial adaptability to litter chemistry (2006) So/7 Biol. & Biochem., 39, pp. 257-267; Duque, A., Carranza, A.J., Los humedales: Conceptos y contextos (2008) Los Humedales en Risaralda: Una Perspectiva Ecosistámica., pp. 17-33. , 1a ed., edited by DUQUE, A. and Carranza, J. A.; Universidad Tecnolögica de Pereira, Pereira, CO; Duque, A., Restrepo, S., Los humedales del Parque Nacional Natural Los Neva- dos en la vertiente occidental de la Cordillera Central (Risaralda y Caldas) (2008) Los Humedales en Risaralda: Una Perspectiva Ecosistimica, pp. 51-73. , 1a ed., edited by Duque, A. and carranza, J. A.; Universidad Tecnolögica de Pereira, Pereira, CO; Giesler, R., Högberg, M., Strobel, B., Richter, A., Nordgren, A., Högberg, P., Production of dissolved organic carbon and low-molecular weight organic acids in soil solution driven by recent tree photosynthate (2007) Biogeochem, 84 (1), pp. 1-12; Gorham, E., Northern peatlands: Role in the global carbon cycle and probable response to climate warming (1991) Ecol. Appl., 1, pp. 182-193; Van Der, T.H., Hooghiemstra, H., Interglacial-glacial Fuquene-3 pollen record from Colombia: An Eemian to Holocene climate record (2003) Global and Planetary Change, 36 (3), pp. 181-199; Heathwaite, L.A., Disappearing peat-regenerat